WEBVTT

00:00.770 --> 00:04.315
Hello friends, I'm Rick Warren, and welcome to Spurgeon's Sermons.

00:04.775 --> 00:09.522
This is the official podcast brought to you by Premier and Spurgeon's College.

00:10.182 --> 00:18.353
You know the teachings of Charles Spurgeon have had a personal impact on my life in a profound way, and I'm confident they'll do the same for you.

00:18.473 --> 00:27.986
So get ready to be challenged, equipped, and guided by Charles Spurgeon, who is universally regarded as the greatest English preacher in the history of the church.

00:29.314 --> 00:36.364
The glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ, Assermon by Charles Spurgeon, part 2.

00:38.147 --> 00:51.227
For God, who commanded the light to shine out of darkness, hath shined in our hearts, to give the light of the knowledge of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

00:51.247 --> 00:55.793
2 Corinthians chapter 4 verse 6.

00:58.237 --> 00:58.898
Note well

00:59.330 --> 01:12.203
how Jesus loved His own which were in the world, loved them to the end, and with what tenderness and gentleness He bore with them as a nursing mother with her child.

01:13.144 --> 01:21.753
For here you see the tenderness and gentleness of God and the love of the great Father towards His wayward children.

01:23.174 --> 01:26.898
You read of Jesus receiving sinners and eating with them.

01:27.554 --> 01:35.666
And what is this but the Lord God, merciful and gracious, passing by, transgression, iniquity and sin?

01:36.948 --> 01:45.340
You see Jesus living as a physician among those diseased by sin, with the one aim of healing their sicknesses.

01:46.161 --> 01:55.515
And here you see the pardoning mercy of our God, his delight in salvation and the joy which he has in mercy.

01:56.937 --> 01:57.458
Beloved,

01:57.826 --> 02:03.733
I cannot go through the whole life of Jesus Christ, it would be impossible, for time would fail us.

02:04.834 --> 02:21.915
But if you will yourself select any incident in which Jesus appears, whether in the chamber of sickness or at a grave, whether in weakness or in power, you will in each case behold the glory of God.

02:23.377 --> 02:27.602
Throughout his ministry, which was mainly a period of humiliation,

02:28.290 --> 02:35.757
their gleams forth in the character acts and person of Jesus, the glory of the everlasting Father.

02:36.758 --> 02:41.523
His acts compel us not only to admire, but to adore.

02:42.464 --> 02:45.047
He is not merely a man whom God favors.

02:45.767 --> 02:47.409
He is God Himself.

02:49.331 --> 02:50.832
What will I say of His death?

02:52.354 --> 02:56.498
I'll never did the love of God reveal itself so clearly.

02:56.930 --> 02:59.534
as when he laid down his life for his sheep.

03:00.975 --> 03:15.776
Nor did the justice of God ever flame forth so conspicuously as when he would suffer in himself the curse for sin rather than sin should go unpunished and the law should be dishonored.

03:17.678 --> 03:26.450
Every attribute of God was focused at the cross and whoever has eyes to look through their tears and see the wounds of Jesus

03:27.074 --> 03:36.749
will behold more of God there than a whole eternity of providence or an infinity of creation shall ever be able to reveal to them.

03:38.291 --> 03:46.724
Well might the trembling centurion, as he watched the cross, exclaim, truly this was the Son of God?

03:49.128 --> 03:55.698
Shall I need to remind you too of the glory of God in the person of Christ Jesus in his resurrection?

03:56.514 --> 04:03.581
when he spoiled principalities and powers, led death captive and rifled the tomb.

04:03.641 --> 04:17.855
That is indeed a godlike speech, I am he that liveth and was dead, and behold I am alive forevermore, and have the keys of hell and of death.

04:19.296 --> 04:25.042
His power, his immortality, his eternal majesty, all shone forth,

04:25.282 --> 04:27.345
as he left the shades of death.

04:29.547 --> 04:34.314
I will not linger over his ascension when he returned to his own again.

04:34.374 --> 04:44.226
Then his Godhead was conspicuous, for he again put on the glory which he had with the Father, or ever the world was.

04:45.708 --> 04:53.298
Then, amid the acclamations of angels and redeemed spirits, the glory of the conquering Lord was seen.

04:54.498 --> 05:04.753
by his descent he had destroyed the powers of darkness, and then he ascended that he might fill all things as only God can do.

05:06.455 --> 05:09.961
I would only hint at his session at the right hand of God.

05:10.682 --> 05:18.493
For there you know how adoring saints around him stand, and thrones and powers before him fall.

05:19.214 --> 05:21.938
The God shines gracious through the man,

05:22.498 --> 05:25.583
and sheds sweet glories on them all.

05:27.206 --> 05:34.398
In heaven they never conceive of Jesus apart from the divine glory which perpetually surrounds him.

05:35.680 --> 05:41.811
No one in heaven doubts his deity, for all fall prostrate before him.

05:42.572 --> 05:48.402
All seize their harps and wake their strings to the praise of God and the Lamb.

05:49.410 --> 05:54.655
The glory of God will most abundantly be seen in the second advent of our Lord.

05:55.696 --> 06:08.930
Whatever splendor we may expect at the advent, whatever glory shall surround that reign of a thousand years, or the end when he shall deliver up the kingdom to God, even the Father.

06:09.710 --> 06:17.458
In every transaction which prophecy leads us to expect, God in Christ Jesus will be conspicuous.

06:18.178 --> 06:27.691
and angelic eyes shall look on with adoring admiration as they see the eternal Father glorious in the person of His Son.

06:29.073 --> 06:30.454
These are great themes.

06:31.536 --> 06:36.102
I will merely indicate them and leave them to your quiet thought.

06:37.344 --> 06:42.931
It is enough to point to a table if men and women have appetites for food.

06:44.453 --> 06:45.074
But now

06:45.506 --> 06:55.258
I will ask you to think of the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ in the same line of thought, only putting it in another fashion.

06:56.440 --> 06:58.923
Treat it by way of observation.

07:00.465 --> 07:07.794
When you look upon the material universe, you can see if your eyes are opened, something of the glory of God.

07:09.156 --> 07:14.002
The reverent mind perceives enough to constrain the heart to worship.

07:15.042 --> 07:17.986
and yet after a while it pines for more.

07:19.128 --> 07:23.715
I have often heard the earth spoken of as the mirror of God's image.

07:24.877 --> 07:44.466
But when I was traveling among the Alps and saw many of the grandest phenomena of creation such as glacier, avalanche and tempest, I was so impressed with the narrowness of visible things in comparison with God that I wrote such lines as these

07:45.666 --> 07:51.153
The mirror of the creatures lacketh space to bear the image of the infinite.

07:52.815 --> 07:59.123
Tis true the Lord hath fairly writ his name and set his seal upon creation's brow.

08:00.385 --> 08:05.812
But as the skillful potter much excels the vessel which he fashions on the wheel.

08:06.713 --> 08:13.682
In so but in proportion greater far Jehovah's self transcends his noblest works.

08:14.562 --> 08:21.730
Earth's ponderous wheels would break, her axles snap, if freighted with the load of deity.

08:23.031 --> 08:30.660
Space is too narrow for the eternal's rest, and time too short a footstool for his throne.

08:31.801 --> 08:41.031
If your mind has ever entered into communion with God, you will become conscious of the dwarfing of all visible things in his presence.

08:42.313 --> 08:43.634
Even when your thought

08:43.810 --> 08:53.599
sweeps round the stars and circumnavigates space, you feel that heaven, even the heaven of heavens, cannot contain Him.

08:55.000 --> 09:00.486
Everything conceivable falls short of the inconceivable glory of God.

09:01.947 --> 09:07.933
When you come, however, to gaze upon the face of Christ Jesus, how different is the feeling?

09:09.294 --> 09:13.778
Now you have a mirror equal to the reflection of the eternal face,

09:13.954 --> 09:18.458
for in Him dwelleth all the fullness of the Godhead bodily.

09:19.659 --> 09:23.683
His name is wonderful, counselor, the mighty God.

09:24.824 --> 09:32.371
He is the image of God, the brightness of His glory and the express image of His person.

09:33.633 --> 09:43.442
If your conception of Christ is truthful, it will coincide with the true idea of God, and you will exclaim, this is the true God,

09:43.618 --> 09:44.820
and eternal life.

09:46.482 --> 09:52.792
Like Thomas, you will salute the wounded Savior with the cry, My Lord, and My God.

09:54.495 --> 10:02.106
Truly, God was manifest in the flesh, not a part of Him, but God in perfection.

10:03.449 --> 10:12.242
In the visible creation, we see God's works, but in Christ Jesus, we have God Himself, Emmanuel.

10:12.770 --> 10:13.832
God with us.

10:15.153 --> 10:28.032
The glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ is most sweetly conspicuous, because you are conscious that not only are God's attributes there, but God Himself is there.

10:30.676 --> 10:36.264
In the person of Jesus we see the glory of God in the veiling of His splendor.

10:38.046 --> 10:40.530
The Lord is not eager to display Himself.

10:41.762 --> 10:46.249
Verily thou art a God that hidest thyself, said the prophet of old.

10:47.411 --> 10:52.338
The world seems to be created more to hide God than to manifest him.

10:53.580 --> 11:03.275
At least, it is certain that even in the grandest displays of his power, we may say with Job, there was the hiding of his power.

11:04.637 --> 11:10.546
Though his light is brightness itself, yet it is only the robe which conceals him,

11:11.970 --> 11:15.394
who coverest thyself with light as with a garment.

11:16.856 --> 11:33.474
If God's glory is seen in the field of creation as a light veiled and shaded to suit the human eye, we certainly see this in the face of Jesus Christ, where everything is mild and gentle, full of grace as well as truth.

11:34.956 --> 11:40.082
How softly breaks the divine glory through the human life of Jesus.

11:41.026 --> 11:45.131
A babe in grace may gaze upon this brightness without fear.

11:46.674 --> 11:50.158
When Moses faced Sean, the people could not look upon him.

11:51.260 --> 11:57.528
But when Jesus came from his transfiguration, the people ran to him and saluted him.

11:59.070 --> 12:02.855
Everything is attractive in God, in Christ Jesus.

12:03.856 --> 12:11.026
In him we see God to the full, but the deity so mildly beams through the medium of human flesh.

12:11.522 --> 12:15.467
that mortal man may draw near and look and live.

12:16.788 --> 12:23.436
This glory in the face of Jesus Christ is assuredly the glory of God, even though veiled.

12:24.498 --> 12:28.583
For in every other instance does God in measure shine forth.

12:29.604 --> 12:35.391
In providence and in nature such a thing as an unveiled God is not to be seen.

12:36.632 --> 12:41.458
And the revelation of God in Christ follows the same divine pattern.

12:43.106 --> 12:50.275
In our Lord Jesus, we see the glory of God in the wondrous blending of the attributes.

12:51.497 --> 12:55.221
Behold his mercy, for he dies for sinners.

12:56.403 --> 13:01.349
But see his justice, for he sits as judge of quick and dead.

13:02.891 --> 13:09.259
Observe his immutability, for he is the same yesterday, today and forever.

13:10.761 --> 13:11.762
And see his power.

13:12.386 --> 13:16.311
For his voice shakes not only earth, but also heaven.

13:17.813 --> 13:28.627
See how infinite is his love, for he espouses his chosen, but how terrible his wrath, for he consumes his adversaries.

13:30.389 --> 13:40.402
All the attributes of deity are in him, power that can lull the tempest and tenderness that can embrace little children.

13:41.666 --> 13:48.714
The character of Christ is a wonderful combination of all perfections, making up one perfection.

13:49.635 --> 13:53.720
And so we see the glory of God in the face of Jesus Christ.

13:54.281 --> 14:01.108
For this is God's glory, that in Him nothing is excessive and nothing is deficient.

14:02.770 --> 14:05.033
He is all that is good and great.

14:06.054 --> 14:09.458
In Him is light and no darkness at all.

14:10.754 --> 14:13.798
Is it not so displayed in Jesus our Lord?

14:15.140 --> 14:16.422
Thank you for listening friends.

14:16.703 --> 14:22.050
This podcast was brought to you by Premier in association with Spurgeon's College.

14:22.070 --> 14:30.162
